# Pixie roadmap

Pixie is intentionally small — a scaffold for the need-singularity Discord
server, not an agent.  The long-term answering role belongs to Anima.
This file tracks the A → C progression we agreed on after KitAstro
called Pixie "a classic bot 🙁".

## Status 2026-04-24
- ✓ channel topic SSOT (config/topics.json) + pixie topic-sync
- ✓ Cloudflare Worker deployed (pixie.dancinlife.workers.dev)
- ✓ /explain slash command — ephemeral long-form
- ✓ Durable Object gateway bot — @Pixie / @ai / !pixie mention handler
  (requires MESSAGE CONTENT intent ON in Developer Portal)
- ✓ Short-reply tagline per project (mentions.js)

## Phase A — public HTTP API  (10 min)
Expose project data as plain JSON so ANY client — KitAstro's agent, a
bash script, n8n, curl — can consume without Discord.

    GET  /api/projects             →  ["anima", "nexus", ...]
    GET  /api/project/<name>       →  { emoji, tagline, long, repo }

Data source: worker/src/topics.js (already authoritative).
No auth; all content is already public.
Single worker; no new deploy target.

## Phase B — (skip)
Don't put an LLM inside Pixie.  An LLM-backed Pixie would overlap with
Anima's role and create an awkward handoff when Anima lands.  Agents
who want LLM answers run them client-side against Phase A / C data.

## Phase C — MCP server  (~1 hr)
Expose the same data as a Model Context Protocol server so AI agents
(Claude Desktop, Cursor, Claude Code) auto-discover it:

    POST /mcp         tools:
                        list_projects()
                        get_project(name)
                        search_projects(query)   (optional)

Reuses topics.js, no new data store.  Client config:

    {
      "mcpServers": {
        "need-singularity": { "url": "https://pixie…/mcp" }
      }
    }

## Phase D — defer to Anima
When Anima is ready for deployment:
- Register @Anima as a separate Discord application
- Anima-agent-core takes over @ai / @Anima mentions
- Pixie stops handling @ai and keeps only topic-sync + /explain
- MCP expands: add `anima-mcp` endpoint for real LLM introspection

## Non-goals
- Multi-tenant Pixie (different servers, different topics).  If another
  server wants this, fork the repo — MIT license, copy config/, redeploy.
- Slash commands with args beyond project picker.
- Analytics / metrics collection.  Keep it stateless.

## Open threads
- KitAstro's agent: once Phase A ships, send her the HTTP URL.  If she
  uses Claude Desktop / Cursor, bump Phase C to "do now."
